  "text": "The dynamical downscaling techniques show larger increases in summer P in the region affected by the North American monsoon than found with the statistical downscaling techniques. Regional dynamical models are able to amplify monsoon effects that are only coarsely represented by the GCM's, but statistical downscaling has no way to sharpen these features. In general, the winter P response seems more sensitive to which GCM was used, while the summer P response seems more sensitive to which RCM was used. A similar finding was reported in [CITATION_1] .",
